NOTES: This is the IBI site for Cataloochee Creek located near the old USGS gauging station. This site is monitored with assistance from TVA and is listed as one of their climate monitoring stations.
This point marks the starting point of IBI monitoring in Lower Deep Creek near the bridge downstream of the Kiosk at the GRSM boundary.
This site is valid and is located just upstream of the Calhoun House. The VS WQ site is located approx 100m upstream, but shouldn't be located on the same  map layer.
This is the IBI site used for the Upper East Prong of the Little River. This site is used by both NPS and TVA. The site is listed as one of the Climate Monitoring locations for TVA's IBI.
This is the starting IBI point location for MPLP. Site begins just inside the GRSM boundary across from the first parking lot.
This site is co-located with the VS WQ Site VS_AQ_EPLR_1

This site was added to the GRSM Fisheries IBI list in 2015. The site starts at the GRSM boundary bridge of Big Creek. The site should be monitored on the upstream right side of the stream. The upstream left side of Big Creek at this location belongs to Keith Hill upstream to the pool junction of Chestnut Branch.

This site was established in July, 2017, for an IBI location. Site begins downstream of the bridge spanning the Middle Prong of Little River, which is roughly 10-meters upstream of the confluence of the West Prong of Little River.
This IBI was first sampled in 2017 starting above the Park Boundary and Cherokee Fish Hatchery.
